#: manifest.ini:changelog
msgid "{language} ({count} voices)"
msgstr "{language} ({count} voices)"

msgid ""
"Version 0.4:\n"
"- Added automatic language profiles configurable from Google TTS For NVDA settings, with per-language voice, variant, rate, pitch, volume, capital, and spelling settings.\n"
"- Improved compatibility with NVDA 2024.1 through 2026 and safer synthesizer switching.\n"
"- Improved multilingual long-text reading with broader Unicode punctuation and no-space script handling.\n"
"- Added Brave as a supported Chromium browser runtime and improved Chrome, Edge, and Brave fallback behavior.\n"
"- Clarified Edge WebView2 troubleshooting and documented custom Chrome, Edge, and Brave paths in the GitHub README.\n"
"- Added an assignable gesture for opening Google TTS For NVDA settings and improved the synth settings ring notice while automatic language profiles are enabled; voice parameters are managed from profiles in this mode for NVDA Speech Settings compatibility.\n"
